Package: spectrolab
Type: Package
Title: Class and methods for hyperspectral data
Version: 0.0.1
Date: 2017-08-04
Authors@R: c(person("Jose Eduardo", "Meireles", email = "meireles@umn.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")), 
             person("Anna K.", "Schweiger", email =  "anna.k.schweiger@gmail.com", role = "aut"),
             person("Jeannine", "Cavender-Bares", email = "cavender@umn.edu", role = "aut")
             )
Description: I/O, processing and visualization of data from field spectrometers,
    including SVC, ASD and PSR (Spectral Evolution). Implements an S3 class
    `spectra` that other packages can build on. Provides methods to access, plot, 
    manipulate, splice sensor overlap, vector normalize and smooth spectra.
License: GPL-3
URL: https://github.com/annakat/spectrolab
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Depends:
    R (>= 3.4)
Suggests: knitr (>= 1.16),
    rmarkdown (>= 1.5),
    testthat
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Imports: prospectr (>= 0.1.3),
    parallel (>= 1.13.1),
    shiny (>= 1.0.3),
    grDevices,
